    So:

    Deque extends Queue

    It inherits all Queue methods

    And adds extra methods (double-ended operations)


    Deque
      â†‘
    ArrayDeque     â† best & most used
    LinkedList     â† slower but flexible

    . Queue = new ArrayDeque<>() â†’ YES, valid

    Because ArrayDeque implements Deque,
    and Deque extends Queue,
    so ArrayDeque IS-A Queue.


    Queue â†’ extends Collection, single-ended operations

    Deque â†’ extends Queue, adds double-ended operations

    PriorityQueue â†’ implements Queue, not Deque â†’ can only use Queue reference

    LinkedList / ArrayDeque â†’ implement Deque â†’ can use Deque or Queue reference




